<TITLE> NSC chief meets club officials </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 21 (bdnews24.com) - National Sports Council (NSC) Chairman and Army Chief General Moeen U Ahmed met officials of 11 clubs of the professional football league at the NSC conference room Tuesday. Two representatives from each of the 11 clubs were present at the meeting and they put forward their potentials and problems to the NSC chairman while discussing how to improve the standard of sports. "It was a courtesy meeting with the NSC chairman after his takeover and we have discussed a lot of things including our problems," Mohammedan SC additional secretary and coordinator of the professional football league clubs, Mustaqur Rahman, told bdnews24.com Tuesday. "We have drawn his attention to the shortage of playgrounds as most of the clubs fail to arrange grounds to practice," Rahman said, "The chairman told us that the NSC has already taken the initiative to solve the field crisis." "We will try to help the club as per our ability, and you try to convince parents to send their children for sports," Rahman quoted the NSC chairman as saying. Rahman said that they sought the cooperation of the NSC chairman to keep games in the field throughout the year. Apart from Rahman, Mohammedan SC senior vice president Mahatabuddin, Abahani directors Kazi Nabil Ahmed, Ashrafuddin Ahmed Chunnu, Brothers Union president, M Jahangir, general secretary Mijanur Rahman, Muktijoddha Sangsad's Kabir Ahmed, Shah Alam and Sheikh Russel president Nurul Islam Chowdhury were among others present. 
